[{"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion Frankfurt am Main S-2230 A - 66 - St II 20 S-2230 S-2230EStK 1978 \u00a7 52 Map 3EStG: 52 / 15EStG: 52 / 21OFD M\u00fcnster S-2236 - 96 - St 16 - 31 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "26 5 1988 Questions of doubt about the transitional regulation according to \u00a7 52 Paragraph 15 and 21 EStG for apartments in business assets as well as filling in Annex W to the 1986 income tax return Responsible for: 1 Reserved usufruct a) Free usufructuary reservation, usufructuary reserved usufruct runs the business. Situation: A farm has been transferred subject to usufruct"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The usufructuary runs the business himself and lives in an apartment on the business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "After the usufructuary death, the owner moves into this apartment and runs the business himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Section 52 (15) sentence 9 2 clause EStG applies analogously"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, the apartment of the conditional usufructuary and the property belonging to it are deemed to have been removed on December 31, 1986"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "However, if in special cases the usufructuary reserved usufruct should be the beneficial owner, the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) EStG apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the value in use taxation of the condominium of the conditional usufructuary, it should be noted that this can be continued by the beneficiary even after the withdrawal on December 31, 1986 until the end of the transition period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "b) Free conditional usufruct, owner manages the business Situation: The business is transferred subject to usufruct and then leased by the usufructuary to the owner (with the exception of an apartment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "For the apartment of the owner who runs the business, the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) EStG apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "With the waiver of the continuation of the value-in-use taxation, the apartment and the associated land are deemed to have been removed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the non-leased apartment of the conditional usufructuary, sentence 9 2 clause of Section 52 (15) EStG applies analogously, so that this apartment and the land belonging to it are deemed to have been removed on December 31, 1986"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Despite the withdrawal on December 31, 1986, the usufructuary can continue the value-in-use taxation until the end of the transition period according to Section 13 (2) No. 2 EStG or - if he is no longer a farmer - according to Section 21 (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "2 Residential buildings on third-party land Situation: The lessee (son) built his own apartment on the land of the lessor (father) before 1987 with his consent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the residential building - regardless of whether it is attributed to the tenant as beneficial ownership or as a material asset - the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) EStG apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The corresponding land can only be removed if the father transfers ownership of the business to the son during the transition period; according to the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "In cases following the BFH judgment of November 18, 1986 BStBl 1987 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "261, are definitely comparable, however, a taxable extraction of the land belonging to it from the lessor at the time of construction by the lessee is to be assumed if the building used by the lessee as the beneficial owner for his own residential purposes is not subject to value in use taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "3 Apartment in special business assets a) Use by the owner partner If such an apartment is actually used by the owner partner, the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) EStG apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The owner is entitled to apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "b) Use by another shareholder If the apartment is used by another shareholder, it must first be checked whether the leasing of the apartment is based on the articles of association or through a contractual contract between the owner and user of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If the apartment is made available through a contract of obligations, the regulation according to \u00a7 52 Paragraph 15 Clause 8 No. 2 applies, which leads to a property limitation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If, however, the provision of the apartment is linked to the articles of association, sentence 9 of this provision applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "After that, the apartment and the land belonging to it are deemed to have been withdrawn as of December 31, 1986, since the value in use was to be assessed by the user in such cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "4 Change of living space after 1986 For tax-free withdrawal it can be (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "In cases of changes in use of parts of the apartment, but also in the case of extensions, conversions or extensions), it is important whether it depends on the existing and the use in 1986 or at the time of removal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "As long as no other apartment is created as a result of the measures, it depends on the living space at the time of removal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If the owner of the apartment wishes to make use of Section 10e EStG for an extension, this is only permissible if he waives the taxation of the value in use of the apartment and thus causes it to be withdrawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "5 Free of charge of the rental of apartments according to Section 52 (15) sentence 9 EStG Even if the fee is less than 50% of the usual rent, the characteristic of free of charge according to Section 52 (15) sentence 9 EStG is not given, so that in the case of partially paid rental always \u00a7 52 Paragraph 15 Clause 8 No. 2 EStG applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "6 Treatment of retirement benefits If an apartment is left on the basis of a retirement contract, the value in use of the apartment - if Section 13 (2) No. 2 and Section 13a (3) No. 4 and Section 7 EStG are no longer applied - is not a permanent burden for the retired person within the meaning of the Section 10 (1) no.1a EStG to be recorded as recurring remuneration within the meaning of Section 22 (1) sentence 1 EStG for the old-age divider"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "This results from the abolition of the taxation of the value in use of the owner-occupied apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand - according to the principles of the BFH judgment of 30 10 1984 BStBl 1985 II S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "610 - in the case of the pensioner, such expenses associated with the provision of the apartment are deductible as a permanent burden, which accrue to the pensioner as recurring benefits in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "In particular, expenses for electricity, heating, water and - provided it is not a conditional usufruct in rem - cosmetic repairs are to be recorded; however, deductions for wear and tear and interest are not to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "7 Possibility of subsidies according to \u00a7 10e EStG for senior citizens 'apartments Since Section 10e (1) EStG requires the use for own residential purposes, the inclusion of senior citizens' apartments is excluded (see also Section I9 of the HMdF decree of May 15, 1987 Income Tax Register 1978, Section 10e Card 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "8 Equalization of preliminary building inquiries with a building application with regard to the preclusive period of sentence 3 of Section 52 (15) EStG. Equalization is not possible due to the clear wording of the law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "9 Non-application of the property delimitation according to Clause 8 No. 2 last half-clause of \u00a7 52 Paragraph 15 EStG in special cases a) Situation: There are two apartments on a farm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "One apartment is used by the owner of the business (widower)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The other apartment is left to the son and his family for a fee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The son works in the father's company due to a tax-recognized employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If the father dies within the transition period, the son could move to the father's apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "So there is another apartment for the son, which according to the basic regulation of sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 52 para 15 EStG has become or could become tax-free private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the son does not move to the other apartment, according to the regulation in sentence 8 No. 2 last half-sentence of \u00a7 52 paragraph 15 EStG and in section A III 2 of the introductory decree of 12 November 1986 (ESt-Kartei 1978 \u00a7 52 card 2) a taxable removal of the apartment previously used by him the result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "b) Situation: A farmer ran his own farm himself until June 30, 1987"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "He lives in the house with his son"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "There is also an old-age divider house in the courtyard, which is also used as such"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "On July 1, 1987, the farmer leased the business to his son"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Since the son wants to start his own household, the previous manager's apartment is given to him to use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The lessor moves into a former farm workers' house that has previously been rented"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The property restriction according to sentence 8 No. 2 of \u00a7 52 EStG leads to a taxable withdrawal of the apartment used by the father from 1 July 1987 onwards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "10 Associated land For the delimitation of the land belonging to the dwelling, the same criteria apply in taxable and tax-free withdrawal cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "According to previous law, the farmer's and forester's apartment was part of the necessary business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The Act on the Promotion of Home Ownership now means that the home of the farmer and forester - like all other owner-occupied homes - is a necessary private asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "For the delimitation of the associated land, the regulations made in the income tax guidelines as well as the delimitation criteria applicable to the valuation law must be used as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 14a Paragraph 1 Clause 6 EStR, assets other than real estate belong if they are more than 90 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "can be used privately, to the full extent of the necessary private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, they belong to the voluntary or necessary business assets if they are at least 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "be used operationally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "These principles are to be applied accordingly to the delimitation of the land belonging to a particular building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Land that is at least 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "is used for business purposes, may therefore not be withdrawn tax-free together with the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "When delimiting the associated land, it is advisable to first separate out the areas that are at least 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "are used operationally and therefore do not belong to the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, this includes - in addition to the areas belonging to the company buildings - all mixed-use areas such as driveways and courtyard areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, the land is to be demarcated, which is completely or more than 90%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "serves the residential purposes of the business owner and senior citizen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "This is initially the area of \u200b\u200bthe property on which the residential building stands, provided it only contains the removed apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "However, this also includes a spacing area surrounding the residential building, to be determined taking into account the circumstances of the individual case, as well as ornamental and house gardens that are in close spatial connection with the residential building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "For house gardens, Section 133a, Paragraph 4, Clause 3 of the Income Tax Guidelines shall apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, house gardens up to a size of 10 ares usually belong to the residential building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "If garages are more than 90 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "are used privately, the associated area can also be found"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Finally, the land is to be assigned where a subdivision is possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The main use case is the base and spacing area of \u200b\u200ba building, which serves both residential purposes for the manager or senior citizen and operational purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "The standard of division is usually the ratio of usable areas (Section 14 Paragraph 2 Sentences 6 and 8 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "11 Annex W to the 1986 income tax return To fill out Annex W to the 1986 income tax return, the Federal Minister of Finance wrote to the main association of agricultural book offices and experts in writing of March 22, 1988 - IV B 4 - S-2236 - 6/88"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "V as well as the German Farmers' Association communicated the following: \"The review has shown that the clarifications brought about by the transitional regulation in accordance with Section 52 (15) EStG make some of the information required in Annex W appear unnecessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Unfortunately, this could not be foreseen at the time Annex W was created"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, it should be sufficient for the taxpayer to provide the information that is required to specify the apartments and their use, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Information on the location, size as well as the authorized users and use of the apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Explanations about the usable area of \u200b\u200bthe entire building as well as about the total area and the areas of the property built on with residential buildings are usually unnecessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "Information on the size of the apartments is also unnecessary, as far as it was given in Appendix L (lines 57 58), as well as for the apartments in line 17 of Appendix W"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, in the case of extraction on December 31, 1986, further information from the taxpayer - for example to determine the land belonging to the apartment extracted - may be required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the specified information about the apartments must also be provided if one takes the view that with Annex W only information may be requested that is relevant for the taxation of the assessment period 1986"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "In conclusion, I would like to draw your attention to the fact that it is in the best interests of the taxpayer to fill out Annex W, since the tax-free withdrawal of apartments regulated in Section 52 (15) and 21 EStG is a tax advantage for which the taxpayer in the case of Unclearness about the existence of the legal requirements bears the burden of determination \""}, {"meta": {"name": "0085545.xml"}, "text": "--- Accounting income tax / wage tax / church tax Hessen"}]